    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03253.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden <choice><abbr>NY</abbr><expan>New York</expan></choice></name>
                    <date when="1877-11-13"><choice><abbr>Nov</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 13</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute><name>Mr. John Lucas</name><ptr target="loc.03253_n1"/></salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>This is to introduce a young man, a friend of mine J Horner Stafford, son of Montgomery Stafford, of Glendale&#8212;He has been for some months studying &amp; practicing Telegraphy&#8212;&amp; perhaps you could give him something to do&#8212;At any rate I take the liberty of introducing him to you, to talk it over. He is a young man of intelligence &amp; first class integrity.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
            <p>I want to come down before long, &amp; make you a call or short visit, &amp; see your works.<ptr target="loc.03253_n2"/></p>
            </postscript>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03253.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
